WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:04.559
That it was going to be useless
no matter how hard he tried.

00:00:05.936 --> 00:00:10.440
I know the whereabouts of
every Asauchi I've forged.

00:00:12.234 --> 00:00:16.071
All Soul Reapers
are given an Asauchi.

00:00:16.237 --> 00:00:17.239
And through continuous training,

00:00:17.239 --> 00:00:20.241
we transform them into
our personal Zanpakuto.

00:00:20.658 --> 00:00:23.661
This is the foundation
and essence of the relationship

00:00:23.661 --> 00:00:25.496
between Soul Reapers and Zanpakuto.

00:00:26.457 --> 00:00:28.000
It is an absolute truth.

00:00:29.084 --> 00:00:31.170
It's not just squad members
and captains...

00:00:31.753 --> 00:00:34.088
but the Zanpakuto
of us Squad Zero, too.

00:00:34.923 --> 00:00:38.551
Even a stray outlaw
like Kenpachi Zaraki...

00:00:39.052 --> 00:00:43.097
gained an Asauchi by pulling it off
the corpse of a Soul Reaper.

00:00:44.767 --> 00:00:45.808
Every one of us.

00:00:46.643 --> 00:00:48.771
Since the dawn of the Soul Society,

00:00:49.021 --> 00:00:53.483
not a single Soul Reaper has
awakened their own Zanpakuto

00:00:53.483 --> 00:00:57.195
without possessing
an Asauchi I forged.

00:00:58.739 --> 00:01:00.281
It was obvious.

00:01:00.865 --> 00:01:03.576
That this method
wasn't going to work for him.

00:01:04.078 --> 00:01:06.914
You and I both knew that.

00:01:07.664 --> 00:01:09.832
He's the only one
who doesn't understand that.

00:01:10.459 --> 00:01:13.003
That's why he needs to know...

00:01:13.212 --> 00:01:15.881
the whereabouts of his soul.

00:01:36.984 --> 00:01:41.781
<i>The blue skies above are hopelessly clear</i>

00:01:41.781 --> 00:01:47.037
<i>At my wit's end, I feel a growing frustration</i>

00:01:47.453 --> 00:01:51.875
<i>As if to laugh at us hopeless cowards</i>

00:01:52.209 --> 00:01:55.628
<i>Countless eyes stare at us</i>

00:01:56.087 --> 00:02:01.968
<i>This soul of mine breaks again and again</i>

00:02:02.260 --> 00:02:05.180
<i>All I can do is hold it tight</i>

00:02:06.389 --> 00:02:11.395
<i>Until the day it turns to ash</i>

00:02:11.645 --> 00:02:14.272
<i>I've absorbed all of this sorrow</i>

00:02:14.397 --> 00:02:18.901
<i>It has shaped me, painted me</i>

00:02:19.026 --> 00:02:21.737
<i>But that's how we got here, right?</i>

00:02:21.864 --> 00:02:26.701
<i>One step at a time, just like breathing</i>

00:02:26.826 --> 00:02:29.246
<i>These countless scars on my palm</i>

00:02:29.371 --> 00:02:31.247
<i>That no longer fade</i>

00:02:31.372 --> 00:02:35.002
<i>Are my badge, my story</i>

00:02:35.294 --> 00:02:38.963
<i>I faced the fear and shred it to pieces</i>

00:02:39.088 --> 00:02:42.050
<i>And let it walk beside me once more</i>

00:02:42.050 --> 00:02:47.097
BLEACH: THOUSAND-YEAR BLOOD WAR

00:03:01.319 --> 00:03:03.989
"KUROSAKI CLINIC"

00:03:04.781 --> 00:03:05.824
I'm home...

00:03:07.617 --> 00:03:08.784
Yo, Ichigo!

00:03:08.784 --> 00:03:10.078
Long time no see—

00:03:11.955 --> 00:03:13.956
That punk ran away.

00:03:23.925 --> 00:03:25.426
What the hell is wrong with you?

00:03:25.426 --> 00:03:26.510
"UNAGIYA"
What the hell is wrong with you?

00:03:26.510 --> 00:03:27.804
"UNAGIYA"
You show up
for the first time in a while

00:03:27.804 --> 00:03:29.014
You show up
for the first time in a while

00:03:29.014 --> 00:03:30.806
looking like
it's the end of the world.

00:03:31.515 --> 00:03:33.393
What are you, some school girl
who had a fight with her parents?

00:03:34.853 --> 00:03:35.854
Sorry...

00:03:42.443 --> 00:03:45.906
<i>I got kicked out without even
getting my Zanpakuto fixed...</i>

00:03:46.907 --> 00:03:49.909
<i>I don't know how to
face them right now.</i>

00:03:54.122 --> 00:03:55.790
Ms. Ikumi, thanks for—

00:03:57.626 --> 00:03:58.877
Whoa, hot!

00:03:58.877 --> 00:04:00.586
Eat it!
It'll warm you up!

00:04:03.089 --> 00:04:04.925
I'm sorry, Ms. Ikumi...

00:04:05.800 --> 00:04:09.512
for not showing up for work
and barging in on you like this.

00:04:18.939 --> 00:04:22.483
I'd rather you came to work than
hear your apologies, you idiot!

00:04:23.067 --> 00:04:24.944
From the moment I hired you,

00:04:24.944 --> 00:04:26.988
I've felt like
an older sister to you.

00:04:27.947 --> 00:04:29.783
You can come to me at any time!

00:04:30.283 --> 00:04:32.286
Kids should rely on adults!

00:04:33.327 --> 00:04:34.329
Ms. Ikumi...

00:04:36.915 --> 00:04:37.915
Coming!

00:04:41.961 --> 00:04:43.963
Huh?
There's no one here...

00:04:53.264 --> 00:04:54.932
It seems like it was a prank...

00:04:55.434 --> 00:04:56.935
Thanks, Ms. Ikumi.

00:04:57.685 --> 00:04:58.687
I'm going home.

00:05:00.855 --> 00:05:02.189
I'm fine now...

00:05:03.317 --> 00:05:04.317
Hey, wait...

00:05:11.867 --> 00:05:13.201
Ichigo!
You forgot something!

00:05:20.666 --> 00:05:22.711
I guess I'll deliver this
to him tomorrow...

00:05:28.132 --> 00:05:30.134
You came to pick me up
in that outfit...

00:05:31.011 --> 00:05:32.303
You know what's going on,
don't you?

00:05:33.637 --> 00:05:36.516
I heard what happened
in the Soul Society from Urahara.

00:05:36.932 --> 00:05:38.851
Including the fact that
your Zanpakuto was broken

00:05:39.144 --> 00:05:40.853
and that Squad Zero came down.

00:05:43.105 --> 00:05:44.774
They kicked you out, didn't they?

00:05:46.526 --> 00:05:48.235
Well, I can see why.

00:05:49.237 --> 00:05:50.363
In your current state,

00:05:50.363 --> 00:05:53.033
there's no way you can fix
your broken Bankai.

00:05:54.076 --> 00:05:57.995
You don't know anything
about yourself.

00:06:09.257 --> 00:06:10.800
Remember what you said to me?

00:06:11.759 --> 00:06:14.971
That you could wait
until I was ready to tell you.

00:06:17.807 --> 00:06:19.309
Now's that time.

00:06:20.560 --> 00:06:21.644
Listen carefully.

00:06:22.062 --> 00:06:23.687
You're not a Soul Reaper.

00:06:24.021 --> 00:06:26.358
But you're not
an ordinary human, either.

00:06:27.776 --> 00:06:30.403
Ichigo.
Your mother was...

00:06:48.797 --> 00:06:50.382
My name is Masaki Kurosaki.

00:06:52.716 --> 00:06:53.718
I'm a Quincy.

00:07:08.774 --> 00:07:10.444
THE SEIREITEI - SQUAD 10 BARRACKS

00:07:10.444 --> 00:07:11.819
Captain!

00:07:12.069 --> 00:07:13.362
Where are you?!

00:07:14.613 --> 00:07:16.324
SQUAD 10 LIEUTENANT -
RANGIKU MATSUMOTO

00:07:17.451 --> 00:07:19.286
I found you...

00:07:20.077 --> 00:07:21.079
Captain!

00:07:22.497 --> 00:07:24.081
Bull's-eye!

00:07:24.081 --> 00:07:26.543
You broke my beautiful tailbone!

00:07:26.793 --> 00:07:29.670
- I'll have to take the day off!
- Come on, let's head back.

00:07:29.670 --> 00:07:31.589
I'm going to make sure
you do your job!

00:07:31.589 --> 00:07:32.882
SQUAD 10 CAPTAIN (AT THE TIME) -
ISSHIN SHIBA
Captain Shiba!

00:07:32.882 --> 00:07:33.632
SQUAD 10 CAPTAIN (AT THE TIME) -
ISSHIN SHIBA

00:07:33.632 --> 00:07:35.634
SQUAD 10 BARRACKS -
CAPTAIN'S OFFICE

00:07:35.634 --> 00:07:37.846
SQUAD 10 THIRD SEAT (AT THE TIME) -
TOSHIRO HITSUGAYA
I've completed the documents, sir.

00:07:38.805 --> 00:07:40.723
Well done, Toshiro!

00:07:40.723 --> 00:07:42.391
Our soon-to-be captain!

00:07:42.391 --> 00:07:43.685
Hold on!

00:07:43.810 --> 00:07:46.062
I should be next in line
for the captaincy based on rank!

00:07:46.312 --> 00:07:47.439
Are you kidding me?

00:07:47.689 --> 00:07:51.151
If someone like you became captain,
the Squad would be ruined.

00:07:51.485 --> 00:07:52.485
I agree.

00:07:52.819 --> 00:07:54.696
I've been making progress
with my Bankai training,

00:07:54.696 --> 00:07:56.531
so I think I'll do just fine.

00:07:56.531 --> 00:07:57.824
Hey, Toshiro!

00:07:57.824 --> 00:07:59.867
How could you
agree with him like that?!

00:08:01.745 --> 00:08:03.370
Take it easy, you two.

00:08:03.788 --> 00:08:04.538
Huh?

00:08:04.538 --> 00:08:06.750
Does anyone know what happened
to the <i>manju</i> that I left in here?

00:08:08.043 --> 00:08:09.418
Captain, by the way,

00:08:09.418 --> 00:08:11.170
there's a report
that caught my attention...

00:08:11.170 --> 00:08:12.797
"CASUALTY REPORT IN NARUKI CITY"
It's about this one...

00:08:13.048 --> 00:08:15.634
Wait. Let's talk about
my <i>manju</i> first.

00:08:15.634 --> 00:08:18.928
Have you seen the <i>manju</i>
I hid in there?

00:08:19.428 --> 00:08:20.721
Shut up.

00:08:20.721 --> 00:08:22.807
Who cares about your <i>manju</i>
right now?!

00:08:23.933 --> 00:08:25.351
It was delicious!

00:08:25.351 --> 00:08:27.062
So you did eat it!

00:08:27.229 --> 00:08:29.272
Even worse,
you tried to brush it aside!

00:08:29.397 --> 00:08:30.856
You're a naughty boy, aren't you?!

00:08:30.856 --> 00:08:33.567
Do you remember the report
from two months ago?

00:08:34.568 --> 00:08:36.613
It's from a mid-sized city
called Naruki...

00:08:37.113 --> 00:08:39.658
where one of the stationed
Soul Reapers died in an accident.

00:08:40.241 --> 00:08:41.743
Yeah, I do remember.

00:08:42.409 --> 00:08:44.203
The one where the cause is
still under investigation, right?

00:08:44.412 --> 00:08:48.416
Correct. We just received
last month's report...

00:08:50.460 --> 00:08:52.962
TWO SOUL REAPERS DEAD
DUE TO AN ACCIDENT
Last month, two more died.

00:08:53.754 --> 00:08:56.799
Hey!
Where are you going, Captain?

00:08:57.008 --> 00:08:59.009
To investigate!
Take care of the rest, okay?!

00:08:59.427 --> 00:09:01.679
Wait, you're leaving right now?
Alone?!

00:09:02.096 --> 00:09:06.142
Yup! I should be back in two days,
so cover for me, will ya?

00:09:06.433 --> 00:09:07.726
You can't be serious!

00:09:07.726 --> 00:09:09.395
Shouldn't we report this
to the Head Captain?

00:09:10.563 --> 00:09:11.730
We're going after him, Toshiro!

00:09:11.940 --> 00:09:13.399
No, let's not.

00:09:14.192 --> 00:09:15.317
What are you saying?

00:09:15.485 --> 00:09:16.610
The Captain went alone because

00:09:16.610 --> 00:09:19.029
he figured this investigation
would be dangerous.

00:09:19.780 --> 00:09:21.740
I know that!

00:09:21.740 --> 00:09:23.493
- That's exactly why—
- That's <i>exactly</i> why...

00:09:24.494 --> 00:09:26.203
...we should wait here.

00:09:27.538 --> 00:09:29.749
At our current level,

00:09:30.667 --> 00:09:32.961
we would only get in his way.

00:09:43.178 --> 00:09:44.179
Any progress?

00:09:44.346 --> 00:09:46.640
No, none at all.

00:09:46.640 --> 00:09:49.144
We've been successful
in equipping Hollows

00:09:49.144 --> 00:09:51.730
with the ability
to Hollowfy their targets...

00:09:52.187 --> 00:09:53.523
but not even the souls of
Court Guard members

00:09:53.523 --> 00:09:54.607
can withstand it.

00:09:55.357 --> 00:09:56.442
I see...

00:09:57.152 --> 00:09:58.153
No matter.

00:09:58.153 --> 00:09:59.278
We are close to narrowing down

00:09:59.278 --> 00:10:01.740
the location of Shinji Hirako
and the others.

00:10:02.490 --> 00:10:04.116
We get to conduct
Hollowfication experiments

00:10:04.116 --> 00:10:05.576
while we smoke them out.

00:10:05.869 --> 00:10:07.537
It's two birds with one stone.

00:10:08.413 --> 00:10:10.914
Let's take our time.
Gin. Kaname.

00:10:11.707 --> 00:10:14.586
Everything is in
the palm of our hands.

00:10:15.754 --> 00:10:18.130
JUNE 4TH, 20:22 - NARUKI CITY

00:10:18.923 --> 00:10:20.674
It's getting cloudy...

00:10:21.176 --> 00:10:22.802
I don't like this...

00:10:23.010 --> 00:10:24.888
The last guy
and the guy before that

00:10:24.888 --> 00:10:26.847
died on a rainy day, didn't they?

00:10:27.139 --> 00:10:28.975
Let's not talk about it...

00:10:29.142 --> 00:10:31.769
I see...
It's dangerous on rainy days, huh?

00:10:32.144 --> 00:10:33.480
That's good to know!

00:10:34.813 --> 00:10:36.149
Captain Shiba!

00:10:36.274 --> 00:10:37.359
What are you doing here?!

00:10:37.650 --> 00:10:40.486
Oh, I was looking for the bathroom
and got lost...

00:10:40.820 --> 00:10:42.489
That's a terrible lie!

00:10:42.905 --> 00:10:46.116
If it rains tonight,
you guys can go home.

00:10:47.619 --> 00:10:49.663
I like to pee in peace.

00:10:55.626 --> 00:10:57.336
SAME DAY, 20:36 -
KARAKURA TOWN, ISHIDA RESIDENCE

00:10:57.336 --> 00:11:00.756
How is everything at school,
Miss Masaki?

00:11:02.676 --> 00:11:03.842
Oh, me?!

00:11:05.302 --> 00:11:08.682
Well, I go there every day,
Aunt Izumi!

00:11:09.014 --> 00:11:12.476
Then how about your Seiren?

00:11:13.561 --> 00:11:15.312
My Seiren is going...

00:11:15.772 --> 00:11:16.855
so-so, I guess...

00:11:18.316 --> 00:11:19.775
What do you mean "so-so"?!

00:11:20.192 --> 00:11:21.318
Yes, I'm sorry!

00:11:21.735 --> 00:11:24.322
Do you understand
the situation you're in?!

00:11:24.822 --> 00:11:26.533
Your predecessors passed away
and you have no siblings,

00:11:26.533 --> 00:11:28.743
making you the sole surviving
member of the Kurosaki family.

00:11:28.743 --> 00:11:31.745
We've only taken you in
because you're a fellow Quincy!

00:11:32.080 --> 00:11:33.081
Mother!

00:11:34.081 --> 00:11:35.082
Please stop.

00:11:35.667 --> 00:11:37.585
I could hear you from outside.

00:11:40.839 --> 00:11:42.340
I'm going back to my room.

00:11:45.677 --> 00:11:46.677
Where's Father?

00:11:46.802 --> 00:11:48.263
He's at Fünfte Feld.

00:11:49.013 --> 00:11:51.599
I too would like to know
when he'll be back.

00:11:56.812 --> 00:11:57.897
- Masaki...
- Hm?

00:11:58.605 --> 00:11:59.606
I'm sorry.

00:11:59.816 --> 00:12:01.359
Please forgive my mother.

00:12:01.942 --> 00:12:03.736
She's taking her loneliness
out on you.

00:12:04.946 --> 00:12:06.780
Don't be silly, Ryu!

00:12:07.282 --> 00:12:08.323
There's nothing to forgive.

00:12:08.323 --> 00:12:09.743
I'm not angry at all!

00:12:10.701 --> 00:12:11.702
Thanks for the meal!

00:12:13.163 --> 00:12:14.163
Oh!

00:12:14.456 --> 00:12:16.666
The shrimp au gratin
was great tonight.

00:12:17.250 --> 00:12:18.250
Bye!

00:12:27.594 --> 00:12:28.595
Katagiri...

00:12:29.596 --> 00:12:31.597
Yes, what is it, Young Master?

00:12:32.264 --> 00:12:33.265
Masaki...

00:12:33.767 --> 00:12:38.645
She knows the only reason
she was brought into the family...

00:12:39.147 --> 00:12:41.524
is because Mother wants to protect

00:12:41.524 --> 00:12:43.985
the Echt Quincy blood
in the Ishida Family.

00:12:44.903 --> 00:12:47.614
Is that what your mother told her?

00:12:48.322 --> 00:12:50.450
You really think
she needed to be told that?

00:12:51.533 --> 00:12:52.994
She's not that stupid.

00:12:54.953 --> 00:12:56.288
Do you think...

00:12:57.248 --> 00:12:59.833
she would be happy marrying me?

00:13:03.462 --> 00:13:04.464
Young Master...

00:13:04.880 --> 00:13:06.966
I see you believe that
happiness is necessary

00:13:06.966 --> 00:13:08.551
for a marriage between Quincies.

00:13:10.845 --> 00:13:11.846
You are so kind.

00:13:14.849 --> 00:13:20.395
Your kindness would be more than
enough to make Miss Masaki happy.

00:13:21.730 --> 00:13:22.941
Don't be silly...

00:13:23.566 --> 00:13:25.527
What's so kind about me?

00:13:27.570 --> 00:13:29.572
I only want to make
Masaki happy because,

00:13:30.114 --> 00:13:31.323
without happiness,

00:13:31.615 --> 00:13:34.118
it is impossible
to look to the future.

00:13:35.537 --> 00:13:36.620
I'm not referring to our future,

00:13:37.663 --> 00:13:39.581
but that of the Quincies.

00:13:49.801 --> 00:13:53.804
NARUKI STADIUM - NEAR SOUTH GATE

00:13:54.429 --> 00:13:55.682
It's starting to rain hard...

00:13:59.143 --> 00:14:01.144
<i>Either they're specifically
targeting Soul Reapers</i>

00:14:01.687 --> 00:14:03.648
<i>or they're just reacting to
high Spiritual Pressure...</i>

00:14:04.816 --> 00:14:06.775
<i>I'll try baiting them out
with Spiritual Pressure...</i>

00:14:09.111 --> 00:14:10.113
Whoa!

00:14:10.529 --> 00:14:11.614
Amazing!

00:14:11.614 --> 00:14:14.075
So this is Captain Shiba's
Spiritual Pressure!

00:14:18.288 --> 00:14:19.288
Damn it!

00:14:19.288 --> 00:14:21.707
The size of Spiritual Pressure
is not what they're attracted to!

00:14:32.009 --> 00:14:34.261
A <i>black</i>...Hollow?

00:14:46.524 --> 00:14:47.609
<i>I see...</i>

00:14:47.609 --> 00:14:49.318
<i>Its whole body is black,</i>

00:14:49.735 --> 00:14:51.778
<i>and its hole appears to be
covered up...</i>

00:14:52.113 --> 00:14:53.405
<i>but judging from
its Spiritual Pressure,</i>

00:14:53.405 --> 00:14:54.740
<i>that's definitely a Hollow!</i>

00:14:59.662 --> 00:15:00.663
<i>I sense...</i>

00:15:00.663 --> 00:15:03.166
<i>a massive Spiritual Pressure
on the move...</i>

00:15:04.375 --> 00:15:06.168
<i>A Hollow... and another one....!</i>

00:15:10.631 --> 00:15:11.924
Don't bother, Masaki.

00:15:13.259 --> 00:15:14.635
How many times must I remind you?

00:15:15.260 --> 00:15:18.932
We Quincies should only head out
<i>after</i> the Soul Reapers are dead.

00:15:20.265 --> 00:15:22.894
And even then,

00:15:22.894 --> 00:15:25.647
it is tradition to let Katagiri
and other Gemischts handle it.

00:15:26.688 --> 00:15:27.731
Think of your position.

00:15:28.607 --> 00:15:31.693
You need to take
better care of yourself.

00:15:32.653 --> 00:15:37.491
We Echt Quincies should not
shed our blood so readily.

00:15:39.701 --> 00:15:40.702
But, Ryu...

00:15:45.625 --> 00:15:49.671
<i>This thing looks like a Hollow,
but it fights like a Soul Reaper...</i>

00:15:50.171 --> 00:15:51.547
<i>It's making it difficult to fight!</i>

00:15:54.801 --> 00:15:55.884
Captain Shiba!

00:15:56.677 --> 00:15:59.389
Karakura Town is under
Squad 13's jurisdiction!

00:16:00.264 --> 00:16:01.307
Run!

00:16:07.730 --> 00:16:12.150
Ryu. You always think about
Aunt Izumi, Quincies,

00:16:12.610 --> 00:16:16.029
the future, and many other things
before you act.

00:16:16.655 --> 00:16:18.658
I really admire that about you.

00:16:19.783 --> 00:16:20.784
But...

00:16:21.326 --> 00:16:24.038
To me,
"taking better care of myself"

00:16:24.956 --> 00:16:27.625
means doing what I can, when I can.

00:16:29.543 --> 00:16:33.214
If I followed customs
and let someone die today

00:16:33.214 --> 00:16:35.173
when I had the chance
to prevent it,

00:16:35.799 --> 00:16:38.552
I know my future self
will never forgive me.

00:16:49.022 --> 00:16:50.605
Katagiri, we're heading out.

00:16:52.692 --> 00:16:54.152
What the hell was that?

00:16:54.777 --> 00:16:55.862
Was it a Cero?!

00:16:56.403 --> 00:16:58.823
That thing is fighting
like a Menos...

00:16:59.656 --> 00:17:04.202
Each time it devours a Soul Reaper,
it's getting stronger and smarter!

00:17:07.498 --> 00:17:10.084
Hey, there's no way
a monster like you

00:17:10.084 --> 00:17:13.880
could go on a rampage without
being noticed by the Soul Society.

00:17:14.297 --> 00:17:15.631
Who sent you?

00:17:16.798 --> 00:17:18.675
Of course, you're not answering.

00:17:20.635 --> 00:17:22.721
Burn, Engetsu!

00:17:28.269 --> 00:17:29.269
What...?!

00:17:40.823 --> 00:17:43.659
<i>That attack was done with
a Zanpakuto!</i>

00:17:44.285 --> 00:17:45.452
<i>It's a Soul Reaper!</i>

00:17:45.744 --> 00:17:49.039
<i>There's a traitor
pulling the strings!</i>

00:17:49.664 --> 00:17:50.665
White...

00:17:52.960 --> 00:17:55.922
He is covered in a black armor,

00:17:56.422 --> 00:17:58.799
yet called "White"
due to the whiteness within him...

00:17:59.008 --> 00:18:00.218
How ironic.

00:18:06.682 --> 00:18:09.309
Don't underestimate me,
you piece of shit!

00:18:23.825 --> 00:18:26.410
You're still able to fight
after losing an arm?

00:18:26.701 --> 00:18:27.662
I'm impressed!

00:18:30.623 --> 00:18:31.624
Damn it!

00:18:38.964 --> 00:18:40.883
Who the hell... is that?!

00:18:42.009 --> 00:18:43.135
A Quincy...!

00:18:43.760 --> 00:18:46.388
This is not a part of our plan.
I shall eliminate her.

00:18:46.388 --> 00:18:47.472
Wait.

00:18:47.722 --> 00:18:48.974
Let's see what happens.

00:18:50.893 --> 00:18:51.894
Bastard...!

00:18:58.192 --> 00:18:59.192
<i>It's fast!</i>

00:18:59.402 --> 00:19:00.403
<i>In that case...</i>

00:19:02.571 --> 00:19:03.698
You idiot, what are you doing?!

00:19:10.621 --> 00:19:11.622
Good...

00:19:12.205 --> 00:19:13.915
I've got you now.

00:19:33.769 --> 00:19:34.769
Are you all right?!

00:19:35.145 --> 00:19:36.689
Yeah...
Oww...

00:19:37.856 --> 00:19:39.901
Thanks, you saved me...

00:19:40.442 --> 00:19:41.943
You're the one who saved me...

00:19:42.737 --> 00:19:44.070
If you hadn't protected me,

00:19:44.070 --> 00:19:45.280
you wouldn't have been
injured so badly...

00:19:47.365 --> 00:19:49.993
Then I guess this means we're even!

00:19:52.622 --> 00:19:54.664
I'm going to heal you.
Hold still.

00:19:54.664 --> 00:19:55.833
Okay...

00:19:56.041 --> 00:19:58.920
But, man...
To take that thing out by yourself...

00:19:59.586 --> 00:20:01.463
Who are you, anyway?

00:20:03.590 --> 00:20:05.009
<i>What should I tell him?</i>

00:20:05.926 --> 00:20:10.513
<i>What would this Soul Reaper do
if he finds out I'm a Quincy?</i>

00:20:16.895 --> 00:20:18.605
My name is Masaki Kurosaki.

00:20:20.650 --> 00:20:21.651
I'm a Quincy.

00:20:29.991 --> 00:20:32.202
I see, you're a Quincy, huh?

00:20:33.496 --> 00:20:35.623
I've never seen a real one before!

00:20:36.123 --> 00:20:37.124
But, wow...

00:20:37.250 --> 00:20:41.253
I feel lucky getting to meet
a Quincy in person.

00:20:45.715 --> 00:20:47.550
<i>What's with this person?</i>

00:20:48.260 --> 00:20:50.805
<i>Is this what Soul Reapers are like?</i>

00:20:52.597 --> 00:20:56.352
<i>I wonder if all the other
Soul Reapers are like this.</i>

00:21:01.315 --> 00:21:02.650
<i>I hope they are...</i>

00:21:03.483 --> 00:21:07.070
<i>Then I'm sure that Ryu, Aunt Izumi,
and everyone else would...</i>

00:21:11.741 --> 00:21:12.867
Let's go, Katagiri.

00:21:13.743 --> 00:21:15.078
Masaki is safe.

00:21:16.122 --> 00:21:18.082
There weren't any problems.

00:21:18.833 --> 00:21:19.834
Got it?

00:21:21.210 --> 00:21:24.755
Yes, understood, Young Master.

00:21:26.339 --> 00:21:27.674
The fact that
he self-destructed means

00:21:28.550 --> 00:21:30.219
he not only surpassed
the target Hollowfication phase,

00:21:31.095 --> 00:21:33.763
but reached the final
metastasize phase!

00:21:34.557 --> 00:21:36.057
And he passed it onto a Quincy!

00:21:37.643 --> 00:21:39.103
What an utter failure!

00:21:40.145 --> 00:21:41.439
That's not true.

00:21:42.022 --> 00:21:44.775
There are times when
straying from the initial goal

00:21:44.775 --> 00:21:46.736
is the superior outcome.

00:21:47.862 --> 00:21:48.863
How exciting.

00:21:49.613 --> 00:21:52.782
A Hollow created from
a dead Soul Reaper

00:21:53.241 --> 00:21:57.788
decided to choose a Quincy,
the polar opposite of himself.

00:21:58.955 --> 00:22:02.167
Don't you want to see
what happens next?

00:22:11.134 --> 00:22:14.137
<i>Everything we had left behind</i>

00:22:14.305 --> 00:22:18.642
<i>Our breaths blending as mist</i>

00:22:18.768 --> 00:22:22.938
<i>without form or expression</i>

00:22:23.064 --> 00:22:27.233
<i>We lie buried as we glare
into the distance</i>

00:22:27.817 --> 00:22:30.195
<i>I can't hear anything</i>

00:22:30.320 --> 00:22:33.449
<i>I can't seem to cut anything</i>

00:22:33.574 --> 00:22:35.951
<i>It feels like I'm sinking</i>

00:22:36.076 --> 00:22:37.869
<i>Falling, falling</i>

00:22:37.869 --> 00:22:38.953
<i>Touching</i>

00:22:39.079 --> 00:22:42.665
<i>Eyes struck wide open</i>

00:22:42.791 --> 00:22:45.795
<i>Something no one has ever seen</i>

00:22:45.920 --> 00:22:52.093
<i>The furthest reaches are now visible to us</i>

00:22:52.468 --> 00:22:56.096
<i>It cannot be undone
and cannot be stopped</i>

00:22:56.221 --> 00:22:59.642
<i>This ensuing struggle</i>

00:22:59.642 --> 00:23:04.438
<i>Whisk it away beyond
the ends of the earth</i>

00:23:04.563 --> 00:23:06.606
<i>Along with our breaths</i>

00:23:06.816 --> 00:23:08.108
<i>Take everything</i>

00:23:08.108 --> 00:23:12.863
<i>Whisk it away beyond
the ends of the earth</i>

00:23:12.988 --> 00:23:14.906
<i>Along with our futures</i>

00:23:15.031 --> 00:23:16.784
<i>Along with our world</i>

00:23:17.867 --> 00:23:21.079
<i>Something no one has ever seen</i>

00:23:21.204 --> 00:23:27.670
<i>The furthest reaches are now
visible to us</i>

00:23:27.795 --> 00:23:31.464
<i>Don't you know God's demand?</i>

00:23:31.589 --> 00:23:34.969
<i>As we tear each other down</i>

00:23:55.780 --> 00:24:01.077
<i>"Even with your sins,
you are like the sun."</i>

